ower supply : 5V switching power supply. the maximum current depend on total number panel. ( with 5 panel i use 6A power supply. ( 60.000 vnd )\r\n\r\nBOM for the adapter board +1 PCB : tme.vn ( 96.000 vnd)\r\n\r\n4x 74HCT245 or 74AHCT245 in 20-SOIC, 7.5mm package which should make it easy to hand-solder. Make sure to get the variant with the T: HCT or AHCT (there are also HC or AHC, don’t use these).  (20.000 vnd)\r\n4x 100nF ceramic capacitor (0805 package) (2000vnd)\r\n1x 10kOhm resistor (0805 package). Not critcial, just a pullup (2.2k .. 15k probably ok). ( 0 vnd )\r\n3x 16pin IDC (=2×8) male receptible to connect the panels. (15000 vnd)\r\n1x 40pin female connector to connect to the RPi. (5000 vnd)\r\n1x (optional) 22μF .. 100μF capacitor for 5V rail. (500 vnd)\r\n( price for 10 board : price_board_order 536.000 vnd ) (attached)\r\nif you dont want use file image and want to do it yourself lets see the tutorial below.\r\nthis project source : https://github.com/hzeller/rpi-rgb-led-matrix\r\n1. download the OS and write to SD card:  https://downloads.raspberrypi.org/raspbian_lite_latest\r\n2. connect to computer SSH, internet and network\r\n3. some comand line and boot setting\r\n4. install led_rbg software and try to run it.\r\n5. setting static ip for raspberry 3 and setting this software as startup software\r\n6. communicate the machine report with raspberry display\r\n( will be add more information later )','info','http://192.168.1.33/index.php/2017/08/16/led-rbg-panel-control-by-raspberry-pi-3/','2019-01-27 21:14:06','2019-02-19 21:11:53'),(19,'Ecocatamaran-Blog Account','chimchichclick | anhvubmt2091@\r\n\r\n\r\ndewayneyoung | !G$O62T$CVa(gtxZ^$BXrKAA\r\n\r\n\r\nducanh | an(^%E(1Etim9YCMcPJ1b$gy\r\n\r\nhungvq | 9ioVufqJj1d!9q#U&@@EZ@s0\r\n\r\ncadboy |  9jQjguvT2T$qz2@1@hthz3&L','danger',NULL,'2019-02-19 20:49:36','2019-02-19 20:49:36'),(20,'ToshibaSDCard','Source code on Github: https://github.com/airlinepilot/ToshibaSDCard\r\n1. Copy source to ToshibaSDCard\r\n2. Plug in 3D machine\r\n3. Connect to the Wifi of Toshiba SD Card\r\n4. Upload the gcode files','info','https://github.com/airlinepilot/ToshibaSDCard','2019-05-18 19:38:06','2019-05-18 19:38:06');
