td width=\"168\">15120</td>\r\n<td width=\"172\">14160.636</td>\r\n<td width=\"125\">38.55</td>\r\n<td width=\"128\">392.28</td>\r\n<td width=\"110\">81.33048</td>\r\n<td width=\"102\">4998</td>\r\n<td width=\"217\">92044.134</td>\r\n<td width=\"130\">924</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n- So, one day we have a total capacity about 92-98 Kw.h need to be saved.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-399 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ecocatamaran.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Picture7-447x400.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"682\" height=\"610\" />\r\n\r\n-so the motor we should choose is 48 Volt or 144 Volt system.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-400 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ecocatamaran.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Picture8.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"184\" height=\"147\" />\r\n\r\n-For 35Kw.h pakage at 48V we need 14 cells = 14*3.7= 51.8V DC\r\n\r\n-1 cell have capacity is : 35kW.h / 14 cells=2.5kW.h per cells\r\n\r\n-So 1 cell will have 2.5kW.h / (3.7V x 3.8Ah) =178 batteries\r\n\r\n-so one battery bank 35kW.h 48 volt have 178 x 14 = 2492 batteries\r\n\r\n- We need 3 of them. so, total we need 2492 x3 =7479 batteries\r\n\r\n- Let try again total capacity we have : 7479 batteries x 3.7V per battery x 3.8A.h per battery = 105154.74 W.h =105,1 kW.h\r\n\r\n-now we try to make 1 cell with 178 batteries. Lets take 180 batteries will be better\r\n\r\n180 =2x2x5x3x3\r\n\r\nLet talk 12x15 =180 batteries or 12x16-12 =180 batteries.\r\n\r\n<strong>When buying a Solar Power system, it pays to understand the different types of technology on offer. There is a lot of marketing hype surrounding the various panel types – and their benefits, so it pays to know what features really matter, and what is just marketing hype before you go shopping!</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-389 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ecocatamaran.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Picture1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"449\" height=\"262\" />\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: separate;\" border=\"1\" width=\"739\">\r\n